Sabor Latino is the real deal ! Romona the owner is absolutely amazing. If you are looking for a true Dominican experience, you HAVE to go to Sabor Latino and see Romona . The hospitality is unmatched anywhere we went in Puerto Plata , Romona is like family , it was like we had known her our whole life . The beer is served perfectly cold . The food was absolutely amazing and delicious, we had a traditional Dominican Republic dinner with fried fish, chicken with gravy and beans with rice and all the fixings . We had dinner with her and her family and friends. It was something we are so grateful for.

Really good Pupusas!!! The ambiance was not the greatest, as no music was playing. I guess I've become accustomed to listening to music in Latino restaurants. Anyways, that was okay because the serenity allowed me to listen to the kitchen and the hand-slapping goodness that was about to become my fresh hand-made pupusas! Let me tell you, they did not disappoint! The pupusas were generous in size and was well accompanied by a cold bottle of Coca-Cola (cane sugar formula from latin america). Careful with the fresh jalapeño pepper in their slaw, it packed a punch. 5 stars if they had a little ambiance going. The place itself a bit run down and the pictures on the wall scream, "I was once a Chinese restaurant!!!". Next order I place will be to-go. Try their chicharron and cheese pupusas. I left my phone in the car charging, so I'll add a picture next time I visit.
